Key Match Events: Jon Dagur Thorsteinsson scored the only goal of the match early on
Post-Match Reflections: Gareth Southgate expressed disappointment with the team's performance and emphasized the need to improve their out-of-possession game
Miscellaneous Highlights: England conceded the first goal in three consecutive Wembley games for the first time since November 1954
Others: Kobbie Mainoo was praised for his performance in the midfield, but England's defense was criticized for poor communication and a lack of intensity in pressing
